<hr width=95% size=5 noshade></center><br>

<center><table width=90% class=top><tr><td>
<br>
<div class=main>


<br>

<p>The metaSHARK web server offers users an intuitive, fully interactive way to
explore the <a href=http://www.genome.jp/kegg/ target=_blank><b>KEGG</b></a> metabolic network via a WWW browser. 

<p>Metabolic reconstruction information for specific organisms, produced by our automated
SHARKhunt tool or from other programs or genome annotations, may be uploaded
to the website and overlaid on the generic network. 

<p>Additional data from gene expression experiments can also be incorporated, allowing the
visualisation of differential gene expression in the context of the
predicted metabolic network. 

<p>metaSHARK is compatible with any web browser with a <a
href=http://java.com/ target=_blank><u>Java plugin</u></a>
(v1.4.2+). 
For full functionality, please ensure that your browser's settings will allow 
<u>cookies</u> and <u>popup windows</u> for this site.<br><br>

<br>

The SHARKhunt software is available to <a
href=http://www.bioinf.manchester.ac.uk/robertson/pinney/shark/
target=_blank><b>download</b></a>, enabling
Linux,  Mac OS X and Windows users to analyse DNA data and upload results to this website for
visualisation.<br>



</div>
<br>
<div class=main>Please bookmark this page, as the database server may change URL at a later date.</div>
<br>
